I"0<p>This release follows v0.0.4 and consists of 115 changes, contributed by
11 people, leading to 121 files changed, 5278 insertions(+), 1916
deletions(-).</p>

<!-- more -->

<p>The source code and selected binaries are available for download at:
<a href="https://github.com/kubevirt/kubevirt/releases/tag/v0.1.0">https://github.com/kubevirt/kubevirt/releases/tag/v0.1.0</a>.</p>

<p>The primary release artifact of KubeVirt is the git tree. The release
tag is signed and can be verified using [git-evtag][git-evtag].</p>

<p>Pre-built containers are published on Docker Hub and can be viewed at:
<a href="https://hub.docker.com/u/kubevirt/">https://hub.docker.com/u/kubevirt/</a>.</p>

<h1 id="notable-changes">Notable changes</h1>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>Many API improvements for a proper OpenAPI reference</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Add watchdog support</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Drastically improve the deployment on non-vagrant setups</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Dropped nodeSelectors</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Separated inner component deployment from edge component deployment</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Created separate manifests for developer, test, and release
deployments</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Moved komponents to kube-system namespace</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Improved and unified flag parsing</p>
  </li>
</ul>

